great new alternatives and awesome works
summary: killing Stalking replacements:
title: killing Stalking replacements:
body:
From 2016-2019 every thursday has been associated with a new KS-chapter, but what now? Here are some great (IMO) new series/manga/manhwa to emerge yourselves in.  

1. Killing Eve: Is basically about a female MI5 officer, Eve, becoming obsessed with a psychopathic assassin, who in turn becomes obsessed with Eve herself. A fantastic series and season two is dropping April 7th this year!  

2. Never Understand/Out of control: This manhwa is about the slow-burn relationship between Yuri (the handsome, popular guy) and Jaerim (the ‘’ugly’’, bullied guy). It’s hate-at-first-sight, ‘till its not and a very interesting relationship forms. I realize that this manhwa isn’t inherently dark, well in the traditional sense anyway. But the manhwa does contain some dark elements, attempted rape and extreme bullying being some of them. I love this manhwa and won’t write anymore about it in case I end up slipping some spoilers in, haha. 

3. Moritat: We are introduced to Jesse Brown, who wakes up in a hospital with no memory of who and where he is. However, when visited by a guy claiming to be his lover, he remembers that this guy tried to kill him. So, basically a BL webtoon featuring some serious mind fuckery. It’s a great manhwa though.  

4. Caste heaven: Is a BL manga about bullying and a cruel ranking system in high school, which pretty much enslaves the lower ranking students. There are heaps of emotional, physical and sexual abuse, so it gets pretty dark. The dynamic between certain characters is very interesting, as there are more than one fixed main character and we get to see some situations from other characters point of view as well.   

5. A love contract with the devil: So, this manhwa is about geeky 21-year old Yoon Han Na, who ends up signing a contract with the devil. Basically selling her soul in exchange for a wish. Things really start to get complicated when her and the devil catch feelings though, not to mention her situation with nice guy and totally adorable Lee Joon Won. Worth a read, adorable and interesting manhwa (not to mention not to taxing on the feels).

summary: [x] // now taking requests for Killing Eve! // request here  Villanelle licked her lips as she looked you up and down, watching...
caption:
[x] // now taking requests for Killing Eve! // request here

Villanelle licked her lips as she looked you up and down, watching as you assembled your sniper rifle before walking across the room. Grinning, she sprawled out across her armchair, twirling her pistol around her finger as she remarked, “You are very beautiful.”

You looked over your shoulder at her to briefly roll your eyes before focusing your attention to the window. When you had first found out another assassin had been assigned to kill your target, you originally saw her as a threat, before realising the two of you were better off working together than against each other. If your bosses wanted someone dead, they were going to get that, regardless about how you got the job done. As long as you didn’t get caught, it didn’t matter. 

But now, you were beginning to feel otherwise about cooperating with Villanelle – especially since she seemed more focus on flirting with you than anything else. 

“Can you please focus?” you demanded, raising your eyebrows at her, and she chuckled, getting to her feet before casually strolling towards you.

“I am very focused.” Villanelle responded, her Russian accent transforming as you realized she was mocking your own accent. Leaning up against the wall beside you, she continued, “How have we never crossed paths before?” 

“I don’t know, but I’m beginning to hope we never do again when we’re done with the job.” you snapped, and she laughed.

“Ooh, feisty.” she wiggled her eyebrows. “I like that.”

summary: Killing Eve Characters’ favorite poems
title: Killing Eve Characters’ favorite poems
body:
Villanelle - “Mother, I cannot weave” by Sappho
Eve - “I died for beauty, but was scarce” by Emily Dickinson
Irina - “Ding dong. You’re wrong.” by herself
Kenny - doesn’t read formal poetry - the lyrics to “Happy” by Pharrell
Elena - doesn’t read formal poetry - the lyrics to “Move, Bitch” by Ludacris
Carolyn - 
Roses are red
Violets are blue

summary: some scenes from Killing Eve I think about a lot: “I had quite a heavy period last week but other than that I think I’m okay”...
body:
some scenes from Killing Eve I think about a lot:

  • “I had quite a heavy period last week but other than that I think I’m okay”
  • that little moment where Villanelle pretends to have a breakdown and then switches back to smiling
  • “I’m going to call you Eve”
  • “I know that you’re extraordinary.”
  • “I just want to have dinner with you!”
  • that little twitch on Villanelle’s face when Nadia called her Oksana
  • the dutch angle shot of the two of them pointing guns at each other
  • the moment where Villanelle sees Anna again and looks like she wants to cry, just a little bit
  • “the best sex we ever had was on that chair” when I say I GASPED
  • that moment where Villanelle sits down, putting herself on a lower visual level than Eve, and Eve slowly, carefully puts herself on a lower level
